# Flint — Testing Requirements

## Rust Unit Test Coverage Targets

| Module | Coverage target |
|---|---|
| Session state machine | 100% (all valid transitions + all invalid transitions rejected) |
| LLM orchestrator | 85% |
| RAG engine | 85% |
| Pre-warm cache | 90% |
| Confidence scoring | 90% |
| Conversation memory | 85% |
| Failure handling | 90% |
| Provider rate limiter | 90% |

Mock LLM providers return fixtures. **No real API calls in unit tests.**

## TypeScript Unit Tests (Vitest)

- All five panels: render test + event handler test.
- Tauri event handlers: mock event emitter + assert Zustand state update.
- Panel layout: resize and collapse behaviour.

## Integration Tests (Rust)

| Scenario | Method |
|---|---|
| Audio pipeline | Mock audio file → VAD → RNNoise → Whisper → assert transcript |
| RAG ingest + query | Sample JD text → embed → store → query → assert top chunk relevance |
| Pre-warming | Sample digest → extract questions → fire mock provider → assert cache entries |
| Session lifecycle | Drive full state machine: IDLE → LIVE → ENDED via Tauri commands |
| Crash recovery | Force CRASHED → restart → assert RECOVERING → READY with transcript intact |
| Network failure | Mock 500 → assert Ollama fallback → assert `failover_triggered` event |
| Rate limiting | Mock 429 → assert Retry-After honoured → assert no immediate failover |

## End-to-End Test (Ollama local — no API cost)

Full session flow:
1. Account creation
2. Health check flow
3. Session design with sample JD text
4. Digest confirmation
5. Pre-warming
6. Rehearsal mode
7. Live session (10 turns with mock audio)
8. Session end and Supabase sync
9. Session review

## CI Performance Gates (Fail PR)

| Test | Threshold | Action |
|---|---|---|
| P95 TTFT directional | > 900ms | **Fail PR** |
| P95 RAG retrieval | > 60ms | **Fail PR** |
| P95 transcription lag | > 2.5s | **Fail PR** |
| App cold start | > 4s | Warn (not blocking) |
| Prompt eval win rate | < 50% vs previous version | **Block merge** |

## CI Pipeline — GitHub Actions

**On every PR:**
- `cargo test` (unit + integration)
- `cargo clippy --deny warnings`
- `cargo fmt --check`
- `vitest run`
- Eval harness smoke test (10 questions, latency regression gate)

**On merge to main:**
- `cargo tauri build` matrix: ubuntu-latest, windows-latest, macos-latest
- Upload artifact per platform

**On version tag (v*):**
- Build all platforms
- Sign macOS .dmg (Apple Developer ID + notarize)
- Sign Windows .exe (Authenticode)
- Upload to S3 release bucket
- Update `latest.json` manifest
- Create GitHub release

## Eval Harness Gate

Any prompt change REQUIRES an eval run. Blocks merge if:
- Win rate < 50% vs previous version
- Directional conciseness pass rate < 95%
- Any domain score < 0.7 relevance
